  {
    "client_msg_id": "8534d6e5-1563-4b4a-90d9-cb6caef8aa61",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Hi folks (and sub-hi to <#CD618THB6|london> folks),\n\nOn February 15th, <http://TOPLAP.org|TOPLAP.org> is celebrating it’s 15th birthday. What is TOPLAP, you may ask? Why, it is of course the “Temporary Organisation for the Promotion of Live Algorithm Programming” (<http://art.runme.org/1107861145-2780-0/livecoding.pdf>).\n\nTo celebrate, there will be 84+ hours of music and visual arts live streamed from all around the world: <https://toplap.org/wearefifteen>\n\nFor <#CD618THB6|london> people, you can attend one of these ‘Algoraves’ (<http://algorave.com|algorave.com>) at Goldsmiths University of London, in their Sonics Interactive Media Labs (SIML) venue with 12.2 multichannel sound and 4 HD projectors: <https://www.facebook.com/events/2376936255659827/>\n\nIf you were to attend such an event, you would witness semi-improvised artistic performances using live programming environments in languages such as C, SuperCollider, Haskell, JavaScript and more.\n\nHere’s to 15 years of TOPLAP and many more ahead!",
    "user": "UEGFXUK3M",
    "ts": "1549295798.864200",
